    "slug": "bricks-minifigs-el-paso",
    "title": "Bricks & Minifigs® El Paso",
    "content": "Bricks & Minifigs® El Paso was recently opened by local residents Thomas and Sara Smith. The couple has a background and careers in healthcare, but wanted to try something different, something fun. There were no LEGO-centric stores or destinations in the area, and the closest were in Albuquerque or Tucson. El Paso deserves a fun store in the city, and when the opportunity presented itself, they took it.\n\nThomas runs the day-to-day operations of the store and has an amazing staff to give all the customers that come in a great experience. LEGO® has something for everyone, and hopefully the community comes together and shares their interest. The customers have come to find the store is a great place to interact with other enthusiasts. This is a safe space to have fun, build and talk about all things LEGO®.\n\nWhether you are looking for new, retired, or used LEGO® sets, Bricks & MInifigs El Paso is where you want to be. LEGO® sets are meant to be opened, built, and played with, which is why used sets are a core department of any Bricks & Minifigs. Bulk bricks and minifigures are also a specialty of the store. If you are missing parts or building a MOC (My Own Creation), you can pick some bricks from the bulk tables to finish your projects.\n\nBricks & Minifigs®, the El Paso one-stop shop to buy, sell, and trade all things LEGO®, opened on May 6th, 2023 in the Concourse Plaza on the corner of Montana Ave and Airway Blvd.\n\nBricks & Minifigs® (BAM) is the largest franchised toy store of its kind specializing in the buying, selling and trading of new and used LEGO® sets, bulk bricks, and minifigures (“minifigs”). The store is located at 6600 Montana Ave, Suite E, El Paso, Texas, 79925 and is the first store opened by franchisee Thomas Smith, a resident of the El Paso area.",
